https://seedjig.com/pre-order/

>Have the same number of seed jigs ready for the number of participants.

>Give them only 24 washers, a hammer each, and letter stamps.

>Have them generate a seed using a standard wallet, like bluewallet.

>Have a referee take a picture of each seed for verification latter on.

>at the start of a horn, whistle, gun shot, each participant will race to stamp their seed phrase into the provided washers using the seed jig and hammer.

>first one to finish wins.

>referees to verify that the seed words stamped into the washers match the photo taken previously.

>this game can be done more generally too. 
>where paricipants bring their own seed stamping materials and race in the same way to determine who has the fastest stamping process.


